com.github.lb.stindex.spatial.sfc.hilbert

Class PrimitiveHilbertSFCOperations

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.tm.stindex.spatial.sfc.hilbert.PrimitiveHilbertSFCOperations
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    HilbertSFCOperations

    public class PrimitiveHilbertSFCOperations
extends java.lang.Object
implements HilbertSFCOperations
    This supports Compact Hilbert SFC operations using a primitive long internally to represent intermediate results. This can be significantly faster than using unbounded representations such as BigInteger, but can only support up to certain levels of precision. For getIndex() operations it is currently used if no single dimension is more than 48 bits of precision, and for query decomposition it is currently used if the total precision is <= 62 bits.

      • normalizeDimension

        public long normalizeDimension(SFCDimensionDefinition boundedDimensionDefinition,
                               double value,
                               long bins,
                               boolean isMin,
                               boolean overInclusiveOnEdge)
                        throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Used to normalize the value based on the dimension definition, which includes the dimensional bounds and the bits of precision. This ensures the maximum amount of fidelity for represented values.
        Parameters:
        boundedDimensionDefinition - describes the min, max, and cardinality of a dimension
        value - value to be normalized
        bins - precomputed number of bins in this dimension the number of bins expected based on the cardinality of the definition
        isMin - flag indicating if this value is a minimum of a range in which case it needs to be inclusive on a boundary, otherwise it is exclusive
        Returns:
        value after normalization
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - thrown when the value passed doesn't fit with in the dimension definition provided
